qas.question: What did Kanye announce he would release after acquiring a Grammy in 2005?

context: In <a2_0>September 2005<a2_0/>, West announced that he would release his Pastelle Clothing line in spring 2006, claiming "Now that I have a Grammy under my belt and Late Registration is finished, I am ready to launch my <a0_0>clothing line<a0_0/> next spring." The line was developed over the following four years – with multiple pieces teased by West himself – before the line was ultimately <a1_0>cancelled<a1_0/> in <a3_0>2009<a3_0/>. In 2009, West collaborated with <a4_0>Nike<a4_0/> to release his own shoe, the Air Yeezys, with a second version released in 2012. In January 2009, West introduced his first shoe line designed for <a5_0>Louis Vuitton<a5_0/> during Paris Fashion Week. The line was released in summer 2009. West has additionally designed shoewear for Bape and Italian shoemaker Giuseppe Zanotti.
